Intuition
Water can be trapped between two bars if there is a taller bar on the left and a taller bar on the right.
The amount of water stored at any index depends on the minimum height of the nearest greater bars on both sides.

So for each position i, the trapped water is:

water at i = min(left boundary, right boundary) − height[i]

If the value is positive, water can be stored at that position.

To compute this, we find:

the nearest greater bar on the right side

the nearest greater bar on the left side

We use a stack to efficiently track these greater heights.

Approach
Create two arrays:

right_gt → stores the nearest greater height on the right.

left_gt → stores the nearest greater height on the left.

Traverse the array from right to left:

Use a stack to remove smaller elements.

The remaining top element represents the nearest greater height on the right.

Clear the stack.

Traverse the array from left to right:

Again remove smaller elements from the stack.

The top element represents the nearest greater height on the left.

For each index:

Calculate trapped water using
min(right_gt[i], left_gt[i]) - height[i].

If the result is positive, add it to the total water.

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n)
Space complexity:
O(n)
Code
class Solution {
public:
    int trap(vector<int>& height) {
        vector<int> right_gt(height.size(),0);
        vector<int> left_gt(height.size(),0);
        stack<int> st;
        for (int i=height.size()-1; i>=0; i--) {
            while (!st.empty() && st.top()<height[i]) st.pop();
            if (!st.empty()) right_gt[i]=st.top();
            if (st.empty() || st.top()<height[i]) st.push(height[i]);
        }
        while (!st.empty()) st.pop();
        for (int i=0; i<height.size(); i++) {
            while (!st.empty() && st.top()<height[i]) st.pop();
            if (!st.empty()) left_gt[i]=st.top();
            if (st.empty() || st.top()<height[i]) st.push(height[i]);
        }
        int ans=0;
        for (int i=0; i<height.size(); i++) {
            int vol_water=min(right_gt[i],left_gt[i])-height[i];
            if (vol_water>0) ans+=vol_water;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};